{
  "text": "Mice were maintained on a mixed genetic background (129/B6/ICR). Embryos were obtained from ICR or Pdgfra H2B-GFP/+ females mated with Pdgfra H2B-GFP/+ males [CITATION_1] . Blastocysts were recovered in M2 media (Chemicon) and cultured for 1-3 days in ES cell media on 0.1% gelatin-coated chambered coverglass slides (Lab-Tek) at 37°C in 5% CO 2 . Decidua were dissected from uteri in D-MEM/F-12 (Gibco) containing 5% newborn calf serum. Postimplantation embryos were processed for sectioning within decidua. Diapause was induced following intraperitoneal injection of 10 g tamoxifen (Sigma) and 2-3 mg progesterone (Abraxis) at E2.5. Embryos were recovered 2-3 days later.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "27090377"
